parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or bucks
the transmission makes a clunking or whining noise
the vehicle becomes stuck in gear
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls
the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearings can cause the vehicle to vibrate, lose control, or become difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud noise from the front wheel
vibration while driving
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause gasoline to spill or leak out of the tank, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gas pump handle shuts off repeatedly while filling the tank
the tank can only be filled in small increments
gasoline spills or leaks out of the tank
and the fuel system venting is blocked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission fluid is dirty and needs to be flushed
and the speed sensors and oxygen sensors need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel odor and leaks can cause discomfort, nausea, and dizziness to the occupants, and potentially lead to fires or explosions.
symptoms: A strong chemical or fuel odor is present in the vehicle
fuel leaks or spills are observed
and the occupants experience discomfort
nausea
or dizziness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities
despite the vehicle being involved in a collision at a speed sufficient to trigger airbag deployment.
